        "edbb": {
          "role": "trading",
          "intro": "A small-pad cargo fit: cargo first, a light bi-weave to survive an interdiction, and A-rated drives to run. Initial is buy-only; A-rated is the trade baseline (~102 t protected); Engineered stretches laden jump range and boost speed so a full hold still gets clear.",
          "callout": {
            "label": "Cargo first, then just enough shield to run",
            "text": "Fill every optional with a cargo rack bar one — a size-3 bi-weave in the smallest slot that still covers the hull leaves ~102 t protected (~110 t stripped). Keep the FSD and thrusters A-rated so a laden Mk V out-jumps and out-boosts the pirates rather than trying to tank them."
          },
          "notes": {
            "TinyHardpoint1": "First Heavy-Duty shield booster — the cheapest large multiplier on a thin trade shield.",
            "TinyHardpoint2": "Second Heavy-Duty booster stacks more raw MJ so the bi-weave survives the opening salvo of an interdiction.",
            "TinyHardpoint3": "Optional / low-priority — Ammo Capacity adds heat-sink charges. Dumps heat for silent running and a fast FSD spool.",
            "TinyHardpoint4": "Optional / low-priority — Ammo Capacity adds rounds. Point Defence shoots down incoming missiles and torpedoes.",
            "PowerPlant": "A-rated runs the shield, drives and utilities with margin; Low Emissions keeps it cool and light for jump range.",
            "MainEngines": "A-rated + Dirty Drives give the boost speed that gets a laden hold clear of an interdiction.",
            "FrameShiftDrive": "A-rated is the single biggest trade gain; Increased Range + Mass Manager maximise laden jump range.",
            "LifeSupport": "D-rate to save mass; Lightweight trims more — life support has no experimental effect.",
            "PowerDistributor": "D-rated is plenty without weapons; Engine Focused feeds the boost capacitor for the getaway.",
            "Radar": "D and Lightweight — a trader needs no sensor range, so claw back the mass for jump range.",
            "FuelTank": "Stock 16 t tank matches the laden jump range; fuel capacity cannot be engineered.",
            "Slot01_Size5": "Largest cargo rack (32 t) — the core of the hold. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot02_Size4": "Cargo rack (16 t). Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot03_Size4": "Cargo rack (16 t). Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot04_Size4": "Cargo rack (16 t). Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot05_Size3": "Bi-weave regenerates fast under fire; Reinforced maximises its MJ and Hi-Cap adds more for surviving interdiction. Sized down to a class-3 to free the size-4 slots for cargo.",
